Magi are combat-capable arcane practitioners trained at the Wizard's Keep near the Cinderteeth Mountains.
The Keep was founded as an institutional correction to the Spirebound Conclave's catastrophic lack of oversight.
Governance follows the Triple-Ledger Rule: every significant operation requires three independent witnesses and records.
Combat role is versatile arcane caster with strong practical field capability alongside theoretical knowledge.
Keep training emphasizes combat application because practitioners who cannot defend themselves cannot conduct field research.
The Cinderteeth frontier exposes Magi to volcanic instability and resonance effects from abandoned experiments.
Magi tend to be more immediately effective in dangerous conditions than practitioners from sheltered traditions.
The Keep operates with independence from direct civic governance.
This is a remort class representing advanced arcane mastery under the Keep's accountability framework.
The tradition explicitly acknowledges institutional complicity in the Conclave's fall as a cultural foundation.
